-- Jordan’s Dealings to Be Cleared March 7, SonntagsZeitung Says
-- B y   D e r m o t   D o h e r t y
-- 2012-03-04T10:05:05Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-04/jordan-s-dealings-to-be-cleared-march-7-sonntagszeitung-says.html
Financial transactions by Swiss
central bank Vice President Thomas Jordan will be publicly
cleared March 7,  SonntagsZeitung  reported, without saying where
it got the information.  Auditors have been reviewing the personal financial
dealings of the Swiss National Bank’s Enlarged Governing Board
members following the January resignation of SNB Chairman
Philipp Hildebrand. The investigation of Hildebrand’s
transactions is expected to be completed by March 7,
SonntagsZeitung reported.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Dermot Doherty in Geneva at 
